Modular Multithreaded String Pipeline (C11)

Build

- macOS (clang): plugins as .dylib, rpath @loader_path/plugins
- Linux (gcc): plugins as .so, rpath $ORIGIN/plugins, link -ldl

Usage

1. ./build.sh
2. ./build/pipeline name1,name2,... < input.txt

Bounded Queue

- Mutex + two condition variables, closeable
- Sentinel: literal string "<END>" propagated exactly once

Plugins

- logger: append to output/pipeline.log
- typewriter: optional per-char delay via env TYPEWRITER_DELAY_US (microseconds)
- uppercaser: to upper
- rotator: Caesar rotation via env ROTATE_N (default 13)
- flipper: reverse string
- expander: collapse spaces/tabs, trim ends

Environment

- TYPEWRITER_DELAY_US=1000 ROTATE_N=5 ./build/pipeline logger,uppercaser

Example with sink_stdout

echo "Hello World" | ./build/pipeline uppercaser,sink_stdout
